  <name>WineCharm</name>
  <summary>A Charming Wine GUI</summary>
  <description>
    <p>WineCharm is a graphical user interface (GUI) application designed to simplify running and managing Windows applications on Linux using Wine. Built with Python and GTK4/Libadwaita, it provides an intuitive interface for launching .exe and .msi files, managing Wine prefixes, templates, and runners, and creating portable backups.</p>
    <p>Key features include support for both GUI and headless modes, single prefix mode for space efficiency, desktop shortcuts, and compatibility with .prefix, .bottle, and .wzt backup files.</p>
  </description>
